value: There is evidence that the formaldehyde collecting on the
chimney of the smoking apparatus is present as
hexamethylenetetramine (HMTA) . However, we have not been able to
detect the presence of HMTA in ETS. The possibility exists that
HMTA is an artifact of the sidestream collection apparatus.
Dr. S. Sears has officially been certified as a
Kepner-Tregoe instructor. Two Kepner-Tregoe courses will be
presented by Dr. Sears to R&D personnel later this year.
